r understanding of US policies in Latin America and their ripple effect on migration. Sanford offers an up-close appraisal of the inner workings of the Guatemalan criminal justice system and how it maintains inequality, patriarchy, and impunity. Presenting the stories of other women who have suffered at the hands of strangers, intimate partners, and the security forces, this work reveals the deeply gendered nature of power and violence in Guatemala.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHuman rightszGuatemala. 0aMurderzGuatemala. 0aWomenxViolence againstzGuatemala. 7aTRUE CRIME / General.2bisacsh  aCentral America.  aGuatemalan criminal justice system.  aextrajudicial execution.  afeminicide.  agenocide investigation.  ahuman rights.  ainternational criminology.  ajustice reform.  amurder investigation.  atrue crime.  atrue story.  aviolence against women.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107913410 cprintz978052039345540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520393462?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520393462423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520393462/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131914-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  a